{
  "video_id": "_jaWs87t5UM",
  "title": "The four fish we're overeating -- and what to eat instead | Paul Greenberg",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12880.0,
      "end_time": 15560.0,
      "text": "So when I was a kid ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15800.0,
      "end_time": 16376.0,
      "text": "this was my team."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16400.0,
      "end_time": 17575.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 17600.0,
      "end_time": 19616.0,
      "text": "I stunk at sports."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 19640.0,
      "end_time": 22856.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t like to play them, I didn&#39;t like to watch them."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 22880.0,
      "end_time": 25136.0,
      "text": "So this is what I did. I went fishing."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 25160.0,
      "end_time": 28656.0,
      "text": "And for all of my growing up I fished on the shores of Connecticut,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 28680.0,
      "end_time": 31880.0,
      "text": "and these are the creatures that I saw on a regular basis."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 32600.0,
      "end_time": 35216.0,
      "text": "But after I grew up and went to college,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 35240.0,
      "end_time": 37896.0,
      "text": "and I came home in the early 90&#39;s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 37920.0,
      "end_time": 39616.0,
      "text": "this is what I found."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39640.0,
      "end_time": 41256.0,
      "text": "My team had shrunk."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 41280.0,
      "end_time": 44375.0,
      "text": "It was like literally having your roster devastated."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 44400.0,
      "end_time": 46416.0,
      "text": "And as I sort of looked into that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 46440.0,
      "end_time": 48815.0,
      "text": "from a very personal point of view as a fisherman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 48840.0,
      "end_time": 50416.0,
      "text": "I started to kind of figure out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 50440.0,
      "end_time": 53160.0,
      "text": "well, what was the rest of the world thinking about it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 53400.0,
      "end_time": 55256.0,
      "text": "First place I started to look was fish markets."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 55280.0,
      "end_time": 57560.0,
      "text": "And when I went to fish markets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 57800.0,
      "end_time": 58336.0,
      "text": "in spite of where I was --"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 58360.0,
      "end_time": 62416.0,
      "text": "whether I was in North Carolina, or Paris, or London, or wherever --"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 62440.0,
      "end_time": 67616.0,
      "text": "I kept seeing this weirdly repeating trope of four creatures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 67640.0,
      "end_time": 68856.0,
      "text": "again and again --"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 68880.0,
      "end_time": 70455.0,
      "text": "on the menus, on ice --"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 70480.0,
      "end_time": 73336.0,
      "text": "shrimp, tuna, salmon and cod."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 73360.0,
      "end_time": 75736.0,
      "text": "And I thought this was pretty strange,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 75760.0,
      "end_time": 77776.0,
      "text": "and as I looked at it, I was wondering,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 77800.0,
      "end_time": 81416.0,
      "text": "did anyone else notice this sort of shrinking of the market?"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 81440.0,
      "end_time": 82816.0,
      "text": "Well, when I looked into it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 82840.0,
      "end_time": 85736.0,
      "text": "I realized that people didn&#39;t look at it as their team."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 85760.0,
      "end_time": 89416.0,
      "text": "Ordinary people, the way they looked at seafood was like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 89440.0,
      "end_time": 91896.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not an unusual human characteristic"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 91920.0,
      "end_time": 95616.0,
      "text": "to reduce the natural world down to very few elements."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 95640.0,
      "end_time": 98936.0,
      "text": "We did it before, 10,000 years ago, when we came out of our caves."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 98960.0,
      "end_time": 101496.0,
      "text": "If you look at fire pits from 10,000 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 101520.0,
      "end_time": 104950.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ll see raccoons, you&#39;ll see, you know, wolves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 104120.0,
      "end_time": 106176.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ll see all kinds of different creatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 106200.0,
      "end_time": 109856.0,
      "text": "But if you telescope to the age of -- you know, 2,000 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 109880.0,
      "end_time": 111776.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ll see these four mammals:"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 111800.0,
      "end_time": 114216.0,
      "text": "pigs, cows, sheep and goats."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 114240.0,
      "end_time": 115455.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s true of birds, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 115480.0,
      "end_time": 118296.0,
      "text": "You look at the menus in New York City restaurants"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 118320.0,
      "end_time": 120216.0,
      "text": "150 years ago, 200 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 120240.0,
      "end_time": 124976.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ll see snipe, woodcock, grouse, dozens of ducks, dozens of geese."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 125000.0,
      "end_time": 127936.0,
      "text": "But telescope ahead to the age of modern animal husbandry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 127960.0,
      "end_time": 129335.0,
      "text": "and you&#39;ll see four:"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 129360.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131400.0,
      "text": "turkeys, ducks, chicken and geese."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 132480.0,
      "end_time": 135550.0,
      "text": "So it makes sense that we&#39;ve headed in this direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 135800.0,
      "end_time": 137330.0,
      "text": "But how have we headed in this direction?"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 137570.0,
      "end_time": 138256.0,
      "text": "Well ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 138280.0,
      "end_time": 140136.0,
      "text": "first it&#39;s a very, very new problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 140160.0,
      "end_time": 143896.0,
      "text": "This is the way we&#39;ve been fishing the oceans over the last 50 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 143920.0,
      "end_time": 149136.0,
      "text": "World War II was a tremendous incentive to arm ourselves in a war against fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 149160.0,
      "end_time": 152416.0,
      "text": "All of the technology that we perfected during World War II --"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 152440.0,
      "end_time": 154960.0,
      "text": "sonar, lightweight polymers --"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 154120.0,
      "end_time": 156416.0,
      "text": "all these things were redirected towards fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 156440.0,
      "end_time": 159856.0,
      "text": "And so you see this tremendous buildup in fishing capacity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 159880.0,
      "end_time": 161536.0,
      "text": "quadrupling in the course of time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 161560.0,
      "end_time": 164456.0,
      "text": "from the end of World War II to the present time."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 164480.0,
      "end_time": 165856.0,
      "text": "And right now that means"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 165880.0,
      "end_time": 169536.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re taking between 80 and 90 million metric tons out of the sea every year."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 169560.0,
      "end_time": 172776.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s the equivalent of the human weight of China"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 172800.0,
      "end_time": 174336.0,
      "text": "taken out of the sea every year."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 174360.0,
      "end_time": 176976.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s no coincidence that I use China as the example"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 177000.0,
      "end_time": 180160.0,
      "text": "because China is now the largest fishing nation in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 180400.0,
      "end_time": 181656.0,
      "text": "Well, that&#39;s only half the story."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 181680.0,
      "end_time": 183560.0,
      "text": "The other half of the story"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 183800.0,
      "end_time": 187136.0,
      "text": "is this incredible boom in fish farming and aquaculture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 187160.0,
      "end_time": 189376.0,
      "text": "which is now, only in the last year or two,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 189400.0,
      "end_time": 192776.0,
      "text": "starting to exceed the amount of wild fish that we produce."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 192800.0,
      "end_time": 196816.0,
      "text": "So that if you add wild fish and farmed fish together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 196840.0,
      "end_time": 200296.0,
      "text": "you get the equivalent of two Chinas created from the ocean"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 200320.0,
      "end_time": 201576.0,
      "text": "each and every year."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 201600.0,
      "end_time": 204736.0,
      "text": "And again, it&#39;s not a coincidence that I use China as the example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 204760.0,
      "end_time": 207816.0,
      "text": "because China, in addition to being the biggest catcher of fish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 207840.0,
      "end_time": 209920.0,
      "text": "is also the biggest farmer of fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 210840.0,
      "end_time": 215376.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s look though at the four choices we are making right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 215400.0,
      "end_time": 216616.0,
      "text": "The first one --"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 216640.0,
      "end_time": 220335.0,
      "text": "by far the most consumed seafood in America and in much of the West,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 220360.0,
      "end_time": 221576.0,
      "text": "is shrimp."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 221600.0,
      "end_time": 224550.0,
      "text": "Shrimp in the wild -- as a wild product --"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 224800.0,
      "end_time": 225416.0,
      "text": "is a terrible product."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 225440.0,
      "end_time": 229896.0,
      "text": "5, 10, 15 pounds of wild fish are regularly killed"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 229920.0,
      "end_time": 232335.0,
      "text": "to bring one pound of shrimp to the market."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 232360.0,
      "end_time": 235456.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re also incredibly fuel inefficient to bring to the market."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 235480.0,
      "end_time": 238576.0,
      "text": "In a recent study that was produced out of Dalhousie University,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 238600.0,
      "end_time": 240416.0,
      "text": "it was found that dragging for shrimp"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 240440.0,
      "end_time": 244280.0,
      "text": "is one of the most carbon-intensive ways of fishing that you can find."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 244640.0,
      "end_time": 246296.0,
      "text": "So you can farm them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 246320.0,
      "end_time": 247576.0,
      "text": "and people do farm them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 247600.0,
      "end_time": 249616.0,
      "text": "and they farm them a lot in this very area."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 249640.0,
      "end_time": 250856.0,
      "text": "Problem is ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 250880.0,
      "end_time": 254960.0,
      "text": "the place where you farm shrimp is in these wild habitats --"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 254120.0,
      "end_time": 255336.0,
      "text": "in mangrove forests."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 255360.0,
      "end_time": 257416.0,
      "text": "Now look at those lovely roots coming down."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 257440.0,
      "end_time": 259536.0,
      "text": "Those are the things that hold soil together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 259560.0,
      "end_time": 263336.0,
      "text": "protect coasts, create habitats for all sorts of young fish, young shrimp,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 263360.0,
      "end_time": 266137.0,
      "text": "all sorts of things that are important to this environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 266161.0,
      "end_time": 269161.0,
      "text": "Well, this is what happens to a lot of coastal mangrove forests."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 269185.0,
      "end_time": 271495.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve lost millions of acres of coastal mangroves"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 271519.0,
      "end_time": 272935.0,
      "text": "over the last 30 or 40 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 272959.0,
      "end_time": 275416.0,
      "text": "That rate of destruction has slowed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 275440.0,
      "end_time": 278400.0,
      "text": "but we&#39;re still in a major mangrove deficit."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 278760.0,
      "end_time": 280496.0,
      "text": "The other thing that&#39;s going on here"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 280520.0,
      "end_time": 284800.0,
      "text": "is a phenomenon that the filmmaker Mark Benjamin called \"Grinding Nemo.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 284680.0,
      "end_time": 287176.0,
      "text": "This phenomenon is very, very relevant"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 287200.0,
      "end_time": 289695.0,
      "text": "to anything that you&#39;ve ever seen on a tropical reef."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 289720.0,
      "end_time": 291376.0,
      "text": "Because what&#39;s going on right now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 291400.0,
      "end_time": 293575.0,
      "text": "we have shrimp draggers dragging for shrimp,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 293600.0,
      "end_time": 295456.0,
      "text": "catching a huge amount of bycatch,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 295480.0,
      "end_time": 299576.0,
      "text": "that bycatch in turn gets ground up and turned into shrimp food."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 299600.0,
      "end_time": 301736.0,
      "text": "And sometimes, many of these vessels --"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 301760.0,
      "end_time": 303135.0,
      "text": "manned by slaves --"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 303160.0,
      "end_time": 305856.0,
      "text": "are catching these so-called \"trash fish,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 305880.0,
      "end_time": 307832.0,
      "text": "fish that we would love to see on a reef,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 307857.0,
      "end_time": 309560.0,
      "text": "grinding them up"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 309800.0,
      "end_time": 310830.0,
      "text": "and turning them into shrimp feed --"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 310864.0,
      "end_time": 314334.0,
      "text": "an ecosystem literally eating itself and spitting out shrimp."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 315120.0,
      "end_time": 317296.0,
      "text": "The next most consumed seafood in America,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 317320.0,
      "end_time": 319160.0,
      "text": "and also throughout the West,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 319400.0,
      "end_time": 320256.0,
      "text": "is tuna."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 320280.0,
      "end_time": 323335.0,
      "text": "So tuna is this ultimate global fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 323360.0,
      "end_time": 326376.0,
      "text": "These huge management areas have to be observed"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 326400.0,
      "end_time": 328335.0,
      "text": "in order for tuna to be well managed."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 328360.0,
      "end_time": 330136.0,
      "text": "Our own management area,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 330160.0,
      "end_time": 332616.0,
      "text": "called a Regional Fisheries Management Organization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 332640.0,
      "end_time": 333856.0,
      "text": "is called ICCAT,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 333880.0,
      "end_time": 337960.0,
      "text": "the International Commission for the Conservation of Atlantic Tunas."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 337120.0,
      "end_time": 339816.0,
      "text": "The great naturalist Carl Safina once called it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 339840.0,
      "end_time": 343950.0,
      "text": "\"The International Conspiracy to Catch all the Tunas.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 343120.0,
      "end_time": 345176.0,
      "text": "Of course we&#39;ve seen incredible improvement"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 345200.0,
      "end_time": 346695.0,
      "text": "in ICCAT in the last few years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 346720.0,
      "end_time": 348456.0,
      "text": "there is total room for improvement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 348480.0,
      "end_time": 351376.0,
      "text": "but it remains to be said that tuna is a global fish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 351400.0,
      "end_time": 354215.0,
      "text": "and to manage it, we have to manage the globe."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 354240.0,
      "end_time": 356176.0,
      "text": "Well, we could also try to grow tuna"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 356200.0,
      "end_time": 359360.0,
      "text": "but tuna is a spectacularly bad animal for aquaculture."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 359840.0,
      "end_time": 362936.0,
      "text": "Many people don&#39;t know this but tuna are warm-blooded."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 362960.0,
      "end_time": 366376.0,
      "text": "They can heat their bodies 20 degrees above ambient temperature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 366400.0,
      "end_time": 368496.0,
      "text": "they can swim at over 40 miles an hour."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 368520.0,
      "end_time": 370256.0,
      "text": "So that pretty much eliminates"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 370280.0,
      "end_time": 372376.0,
      "text": "all the advantages of farming a fish, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 372400.0,
      "end_time": 373616.0,
      "text": "A farmed fish is --"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 373640.0,
      "end_time": 376680.0,
      "text": "or a fish is cold-blooded, it doesn&#39;t move too much."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 376930.0,
      "end_time": 378960.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a great thing for growing protein."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 378120.0,
      "end_time": 380456.0,
      "text": "But if you&#39;ve got this crazy, wild creature"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 380480.0,
      "end_time": 382976.0,
      "text": "that swims at 40 miles an hour and heats its blood --"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 383000.0,
      "end_time": 385320.0,
      "text": "not a great candidate for aquaculture."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 385760.0,
      "end_time": 386976.0,
      "text": "The next creature --"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 387000.0,
      "end_time": 389976.0,
      "text": "most consumed seafood in America and throughout the West --"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 390000.0,
      "end_time": 391216.0,
      "text": "is salmon."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 391240.0,
      "end_time": 393416.0,
      "text": "Now salmon got its plundering, too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 393440.0,
      "end_time": 396576.0,
      "text": "but it didn&#39;t really necessarily happen through fishing."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 396600.0,
      "end_time": 398376.0,
      "text": "This is my home state of Connecticut."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 398400.0,
      "end_time": 401455.0,
      "text": "Connecticut used to be home to a lot of wild salmon."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 401480.0,
      "end_time": 403536.0,
      "text": "But if you look at this map of Connecticut,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 403560.0,
      "end_time": 406560.0,
      "text": "every dot on that map is a dam."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 407400.0,
      "end_time": 411256.0,
      "text": "There are over 3,000 dams in the state of Connecticut."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 411280.0,
      "end_time": 414816.0,
      "text": "I often say this is why people in Connecticut are so uptight --"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 414840.0,
      "end_time": 416416.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 416440.0,
      "end_time": 419976.0,
      "text": "If somebody could just unblock Connecticut&#39;s chi,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 420000.0,
      "end_time": 422496.0,
      "text": "I feel that we could have an infinitely better world."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 422520.0,
      "end_time": 424256.0,
      "text": "But I made this particular comment"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 424280.0,
      "end_time": 426936.0,
      "text": "at a convention once of national parks officers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 426960.0,
      "end_time": 429695.0,
      "text": "and this guy from North Carolina sidled up to me, he says,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 429720.0,
      "end_time": 433160.0,
      "text": "\"You know, you oughtn&#39;t be so hard on your Connecticut,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 433400.0,
      "end_time": 437856.0,
      "text": "cause we here in North Carolina, we got 35,000 dams.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 437880.0,
      "end_time": 440736.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s a national epidemic, it&#39;s an international epidemic."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 440760.0,
      "end_time": 442216.0,
      "text": "And there are dams everywhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 442240.0,
      "end_time": 443896.0,
      "text": "and these are precisely the things"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 443920.0,
      "end_time": 446696.0,
      "text": "that stop wild salmon from reaching their spawning grounds."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 446720.0,
      "end_time": 448816.0,
      "text": "So as a result, we&#39;ve turned to aquaculture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 448840.0,
      "end_time": 452496.0,
      "text": "and salmon is one the most successful, at least from a numbers point of view."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 452520.0,
      "end_time": 454736.0,
      "text": "When they first started farming salmon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 454760.0,
      "end_time": 457695.0,
      "text": "it could take as many as six pounds of wild fish"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 457720.0,
      "end_time": 459896.0,
      "text": "to make a single pound of salmon."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 459920.0,
      "end_time": 462576.0,
      "text": "The industry has, to its credit, greatly improved."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 462600.0,
      "end_time": 464267.0,
      "text": "They&#39;ve gotten it below two to one,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 464291.0,
      "end_time": 466576.0,
      "text": "although it&#39;s a little bit of a cheat"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 466600.0,
      "end_time": 469416.0,
      "text": "because if you look at the way aquaculture feed is produced,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 469440.0,
      "end_time": 470896.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re measuring pellets --"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 470920.0,
      "end_time": 473176.0,
      "text": "pounds of pellets per pound of salmon."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 473200.0,
      "end_time": 475856.0,
      "text": "Those pellets are in turn reduced fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 475880.0,
      "end_time": 479376.0,
      "text": "So the actual -- what&#39;s called the FIFO, the fish in and the fish out --"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 479400.0,
      "end_time": 480736.0,
      "text": "kind of hard to say."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 480760.0,
      "end_time": 481976.0,
      "text": "But in any case,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 482000.0,
      "end_time": 483216.0,
      "text": "credit to the industry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 483240.0,
      "end_time": 485816.0,
      "text": "it has lowered the amount of fish per pound of salmon."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 485840.0,
      "end_time": 488150.0,
      "text": "Problem is we&#39;ve also gone crazy"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 488400.0,
      "end_time": 490256.0,
      "text": "with the amount of salmon that we&#39;re producing."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 490280.0,
      "end_time": 493895.0,
      "text": "Aquaculture is the fastest growing food system on the planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 493920.0,
      "end_time": 496896.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s growing at something like seven percent per year."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 496920.0,
      "end_time": 500936.0,
      "text": "And so even though we&#39;re doing less per fish"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 500960.0,
      "end_time": 502256.0,
      "text": "to bring it to the market,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 502280.0,
      "end_time": 505150.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re still killing a lot of these little fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 505400.0,
      "end_time": 508216.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s not just fish that we&#39;re feeding fish to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 508240.0,
      "end_time": 510840.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re also feeding fish to chickens and pigs."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 511600.0,
      "end_time": 514536.0,
      "text": "So we&#39;ve got chickens and they&#39;re eating fish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 514558.99999999994,
      "end_time": 518814.99999999994,
      "text": "but weirdly, we also have fish that are eating chickens."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 518840.00000000006,
      "end_time": 521936.00000000006,
      "text": "Because the byproducts of chickens -- feathers, blood, bone --"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 521960.00000000006,
      "end_time": 524256.00000000006,
      "text": "get ground up and fed to fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 524280.0,
      "end_time": 525496.0,
      "text": "So I often wonder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 525520.0,
      "end_time": 528760.0,
      "text": "is there a fish that ate a chicken that ate a fish?"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 529360.0,
      "end_time": 532376.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s sort of a reworking of the chicken and egg thing. Anyway --"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 532400.0,
      "end_time": 533496.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 533520.0,
      "end_time": 536295.0,
      "text": "All together, though, it results in a terrible mess."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 536320.0,
      "end_time": 537696.0,
      "text": "What you&#39;re talking about"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 537720.0,
      "end_time": 543376.0,
      "text": "is something between 20 and 30 million metric tons of wild creatures"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 543400.0,
      "end_time": 546376.0,
      "text": "that are taken from the ocean and used and ground up."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 546400.0,
      "end_time": 548456.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s the equivalent of a third of a China,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 548480.0,
      "end_time": 550536.0,
      "text": "or of an entire United States of humans"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 550560.0,
      "end_time": 552959.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s taken out of the sea each and every year."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 554160.0,
      "end_time": 556695.0,
      "text": "The last of the four is a kind of amorphous thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 556720.0,
      "end_time": 560216.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s what the industry calls \"whitefish.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 560240.0,
      "end_time": 563216.0,
      "text": "There are many fish that get cycled into this whitefish thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 563240.0,
      "end_time": 565456.0,
      "text": "but the way to kind of tell the story, I think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 565480.0,
      "end_time": 568416.0,
      "text": "is through that classic piece of American culinary innovation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 568440.0,
      "end_time": 569816.0,
      "text": "the Filet-O-Fish sandwich."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 569840.0,
      "end_time": 572816.0,
      "text": "So the Filet-O-Fish sandwich actually started as halibut."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 572840.0,
      "end_time": 575176.0,
      "text": "And it started because a local franchise owner"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 575200.0,
      "end_time": 580736.0,
      "text": "found that when he served his McDonald&#39;s on Friday, nobody came."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 580760.0,
      "end_time": 583295.0,
      "text": "Because it was a Catholic community, they needed fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 583320.0,
      "end_time": 585176.0,
      "text": "So he went to Ray Kroc and he said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 585200.0,
      "end_time": 588696.0,
      "text": "\"I&#39;m going to bring you a fish sandwich, going to be made out of halibut.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 588720.0,
      "end_time": 591160.0,
      "text": "Ray Kroc said, \"I don&#39;t think it&#39;s going to work."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 591400.0,
      "end_time": 592336.0,
      "text": "I want to do a Hula Burger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 592360.0,
      "end_time": 594884.0,
      "text": "and there&#39;s going to be a slice of pineapple on a bun."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 594908.0,
      "end_time": 596644.0,
      "text": "But let&#39;s do this, let&#39;s have a bet."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 596668.0,
      "end_time": 600176.0,
      "text": "Whosever sandwich sells more, that will be the winning sandwich.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 600200.0,
      "end_time": 604536.0,
      "text": "Well, it&#39;s kind of sad for the ocean that the Hula Burger didn&#39;t win."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 604560.0,
      "end_time": 606695.0,
      "text": "So he made his halibut sandwich."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 606720.0,
      "end_time": 610560.0,
      "text": "Unfortunately though, the sandwich came in at 30 cents."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 610800.0,
      "end_time": 612616.0,
      "text": "Ray wanted the sandwich to come in at 25 cents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 612640.0,
      "end_time": 614576.0,
      "text": "so he turned to Atlantic cod."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 614600.0,
      "end_time": 617376.0,
      "text": "We all know what happened to Atlantic cod in New England."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 617400.0,
      "end_time": 620896.0,
      "text": "So now the Filet-O-Fish sandwich is made out of Alaska pollock,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 620920.0,
      "end_time": 623656.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s the largest fin fish fishery in the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 623680.0,
      "end_time": 628550.0,
      "text": "2 to 3 billion pounds of fish taken out of the sea every single year."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 628800.0,
      "end_time": 629616.0,
      "text": "If we go through the pollock,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 629640.0,
      "end_time": 632960.0,
      "text": "the next choice is probably going to be tilapia."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 632120.0,
      "end_time": 635960.0,
      "text": "Tilapia is one of those fish nobody ever heard of 20 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 635120.0,
      "end_time": 639376.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s actually a very efficient converter of plant protein into animal protein,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 639400.0,
      "end_time": 641456.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s been a godsend to the third world."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 641480.0,
      "end_time": 643856.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s actually a tremendously sustainable solution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 643880.0,
      "end_time": 646960.0,
      "text": "it goes from an egg to an adult in nine months."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 646120.0,
      "end_time": 648456.0,
      "text": "The problem is that when you look about the West,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 648480.0,
      "end_time": 650496.0,
      "text": "it doesn&#39;t do what the West wants it to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 650520.0,
      "end_time": 653256.0,
      "text": "It really doesn&#39;t have what&#39;s called an oily fish profile."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 653280.0,
      "end_time": 655656.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t have the EPA and DHA omega-3s"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 655680.0,
      "end_time": 658976.0,
      "text": "that we all think are going to make us live forever."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 659000.0,
      "end_time": 660496.0,
      "text": "So what do we do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 660520.0,
      "end_time": 663696.0,
      "text": "I mean, first of all, what about this poor fish, the clupeids?"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 663720.0,
      "end_time": 668160.0,
      "text": "The fish that represent a huge part of that 20 to 30 million metric tons."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 668760.0,
      "end_time": 671816.0,
      "text": "Well, one possibility that a lot of conservationists have raised"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 671840.0,
      "end_time": 673456.0,
      "text": "is could we eat them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 673480.0,
      "end_time": 676376.0,
      "text": "Could we eat them directly instead of feeding them to salmon?"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 676400.0,
      "end_time": 677736.0,
      "text": "There are arguments for it."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 677760.0,
      "end_time": 680380.0,
      "text": "They are tremendously fuel efficient to bring to market,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 680404.0,
      "end_time": 682496.0,
      "text": "a fraction of the fuel cost of say, shrimp,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 682520.0,
      "end_time": 685856.0,
      "text": "and at the very top of the carbon efficiency scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 685880.0,
      "end_time": 690160.0,
      "text": "They also are omega-3 rich, a great source for EPA and DHA."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 690400.0,
      "end_time": 691496.0,
      "text": "So that is a potential."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 691520.0,
      "end_time": 695216.0,
      "text": "And if we were to go down that route what I would say is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 695240.0,
      "end_time": 699560.0,
      "text": "instead of paying a few bucks a pound -- or a few bucks a ton, really --"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 699800.0,
      "end_time": 701560.0,
      "text": "and making it into aquafeed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 701800.0,
      "end_time": 704376.0,
      "text": "could we halve the catch and double the price for the fishermen"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 704400.0,
      "end_time": 708520.0,
      "text": "and make that our way of treating these particular fish?"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 709200.0,
      "end_time": 711896.0,
      "text": "Other possibility though, which is much more interesting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 711920.0,
      "end_time": 714295.0,
      "text": "is looking at bivalves, particularly mussels."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 714320.0,
      "end_time": 719256.0,
      "text": "Now, mussels are very high in EPA and DHA, they&#39;re similar to canned tuna."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 719280.0,
      "end_time": 721216.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re also extremely fuel efficient."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 721240.0,
      "end_time": 723560.0,
      "text": "To bring a pound of mussels to market"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 723800.0,
      "end_time": 726696.0,
      "text": "is about a thirtieth of the carbon as required to bring beef to market."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 726720.0,
      "end_time": 728296.0,
      "text": "They require no forage fish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 728320.0,
      "end_time": 732576.0,
      "text": "they actually get their omega-3s by filtering the water of microalgae."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 732600.0,
      "end_time": 735816.0,
      "text": "In fact, that&#39;s where omega-3s come from, they don&#39;t come from fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 735840.0,
      "end_time": 739896.0,
      "text": "Microalgae make the omega-3s, they&#39;re only bioconcentrated in fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 739920.0,
      "end_time": 741175.0,
      "text": "Mussels and other bivalves"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 741200.0,
      "end_time": 743200.0,
      "text": "do tremendous amounts of water filtration."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 743224.0,
      "end_time": 746776.0,
      "text": "A single mussel can filter dozens of gallons every single day."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 746800.0,
      "end_time": 749575.0,
      "text": "And this is incredibly important when we look at the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 749600.0,
      "end_time": 753176.0,
      "text": "Right now, nitrification, overuse of phosphates in our waterways"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 753200.0,
      "end_time": 755536.0,
      "text": "are causing tremendous algal blooms."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 755560.0,
      "end_time": 759815.0,
      "text": "Over 400 new dead zones have been created in the last 20 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 759840.0,
      "end_time": 763440.0,
      "text": "tremendous sources of marine life death."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 764320.0,
      "end_time": 766496.0,
      "text": "We also could look at not a fish at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 766520.0,
      "end_time": 767936.0,
      "text": "We could look at a vegetable."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 767960.0,
      "end_time": 769696.0,
      "text": "We could look at seaweed, the kelps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 769720.0,
      "end_time": 773560.0,
      "text": "all these different varieties of things that can be high in omega-3s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 773800.0,
      "end_time": 774376.0,
      "text": "can be high in proteins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 774400.0,
      "end_time": 776160.0,
      "text": "tremendously good things."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 776400.0,
      "end_time": 778695.0,
      "text": "They filter the water just like mussels do."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 778720.0,
      "end_time": 779976.0,
      "text": "And weirdly enough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 780000.0,
      "end_time": 782616.0,
      "text": "it turns out that you can actually feed this to cows."
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 782640.0,
      "end_time": 784856.0,
      "text": "Now, I&#39;m not a big fan of cattle."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 784880.0,
      "end_time": 786816.0,
      "text": "But if you wanted to keep growing cattle"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 786840.0,
      "end_time": 789656.0,
      "text": "in a time and place where water resources are limited,"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 789680.0,
      "end_time": 792776.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re growing seaweed in the water, you don&#39;t have to water it --"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 792800.0,
      "end_time": 794455.0,
      "text": "major consideration."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 794480.0,
      "end_time": 797216.0,
      "text": "And the last fish is a question mark."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 797240.0,
      "end_time": 801960.0,
      "text": "We have the ability to create aquacultured fish"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 801120.0,
      "end_time": 804536.0,
      "text": "that creates a net gain of marine protein for us."
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 804560.0,
      "end_time": 806695.0,
      "text": "This creature would have to be vegetarian,"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 806720.0,
      "end_time": 808496.0,
      "text": "it would have to be fast growing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 808520.0,
      "end_time": 811175.0,
      "text": "it would have to be adaptable to a changing climate"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 811200.0,
      "end_time": 813536.0,
      "text": "and it would have to have that oily fish profile,"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 813560.0,
      "end_time": 817455.0,
      "text": "that EPA, DHA, omega-3 fatty acid profile that we&#39;re looking for."
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 817480.0,
      "end_time": 820416.0,
      "text": "This exists kind of on paper."
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 820440.0,
      "end_time": 824560.0,
      "text": "I have been reporting on these subjects for 15 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 824800.0,
      "end_time": 826976.0,
      "text": "Every time I do a new story, somebody tells me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 827000.0,
      "end_time": 829856.0,
      "text": "\"We can do all that. We can do it. We&#39;ve figured it all out."
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 829880.0,
      "end_time": 831960.0,
      "text": "We can produce a fish"
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 831120.0,
      "end_time": 833696.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s a net gain of marine protein and has omega-3s.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 833720.0,
      "end_time": 834936.0,
      "text": "Great."
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 834960.0,
      "end_time": 837960.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t seem to be getting scaled up."
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 837120.0,
      "end_time": 838856.0,
      "text": "It is time to scale this up."
    },
    {
      "index": 317,
      "start_time": 838880.0,
      "end_time": 840960.0,
      "text": "If we do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 318,
      "start_time": 840120.0,
      "end_time": 843616.0,
      "text": "30 million metric tons of seafood, a third of the world catch,"
    },
    {
      "index": 319,
      "start_time": 843640.0,
      "end_time": 844840.0,
      "text": "stays in the water."
    },
    {
      "index": 320,
      "start_time": 845880.0,
      "end_time": 849176.0,
      "text": "So I guess what I&#39;m saying is this is what we&#39;ve been going with."
    },
    {
      "index": 321,
      "start_time": 849200.0,
      "end_time": 852376.0,
      "text": "We tend to go with our appetites rather than our minds."
    },
    {
      "index": 322,
      "start_time": 852400.0,
      "end_time": 855896.0,
      "text": "But if we went with this, or some configuration of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 323,
      "start_time": 855920.0,
      "end_time": 857635.0,
      "text": "we might have a little more of this."
    },
    {
      "index": 324,
      "start_time": 859120.0,
      "end_time": 860336.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 325,
      "start_time": 860360.0,
      "end_time": 862840.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}